v0.38.0: a real planetary sky (no more 2D-plane feel)

- the sky dome, all deep-space objects, and the moon now follow the camera, so the viewer is always at the centre of the celestial sphere — zero parallax when you orbit, like an infinitely distant sky
- deep-space materials (galaxies, nebulae, meteors, constellations) opt out of ground fog so they stay crisp at the fixed dome distance
- fixes the report that stars felt fixed to a flat plane when rotating
